description._content: Description: 29. Showing area of Fresh Water Lake reclaimed by Eucalyptus which are now ripe for first felling in and area urgently needing local supplies of fuel and timber. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: 30. General view of the large area of unproductive Marshland at Limassol swamp capable of forest reclamation which is at present an acute malarial problem and only supports rough grazing and reed production. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
